OL,3,CWelsh Government face legal challenge
OL,4,Cover #205m Cardiff Airport subsidy
OL,6,FBristol Airport has asked a tribunal
OL,7,Fto quash the Welsh Government's
OL,8,Fdecision to give a #205 million
OL,9,Fsubsidy to Cardiff Airport.
OL,11,FAt the opening of a two-day
OL,12,FCompetition Appeal Tribunal hearing in
OL,13,FCardiff, Bristol Airport said the
OL,14,Fsupport is 'unlawful' and 'distorts
OL,15,Fcompetition between the two airports'.
OL,17,FIn 2025, Cardiff Airport was awarded
OL,18,Fthe subsidy to be given over the next
OL,19,Fdecade, which Welsh Government
OL,20,Fministers said at the time was vital
OL,21,Fto bring long-term economic growth.
