OL,3,CWelsh Government face legal challenge
OL,4,Cover #205m Cardiff Airport subsidy
OL,6,FBristol Airport's legal team has
OL,7,Fargued that Cardiff Airport has
OL,8,Falready received significant public
OL,9,Ffunding in recent years and that the
OL,10,Flatest subsidy breaches principles set
OL,11,Fout in the Subsidy Control Act 2022,
OL,12,Fparticularly around providing repeated
OL,13,Fsupport to what it describes as an
OL,14,F"ailing" business.
OL,16,FIt argues the money is propping up
OL,17,Fwhat it describes as a failing
OL,18,Fbusiness and that ministers did not
OL,19,Fproperly assess the impact the subsidy
OL,20,Fwould have on competition.
