OL,4,Cover #205m Cardiff Airport subsidy
OL,6,FThe Welsh Government has previously
OL,7,Freceived criticism from the
OL,8,FCompetition and Markets Authority's
OL,9,FSubsidy Advice Unit, which raised
OL,10,Fconcerns about "unevidenced
OL,11,Fassumptions" when the support package
OL,12,Fwas first announced.
OL,14,FCardiff Airport is owned by the Welsh
OL,15,FGovernment and is often described by
OL,16,Fministers as a key piece of national
OL,17,Finfrastructure, important for
OL,18,Fconnectivity, jobs and inward
OL,19,Finvestment.
